                    <p>VISIT</p>
                    <h2>Victoria Memorial</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Victoria Memorial in Kolkata is a grand marble building dedicated to Queen Victoria, blending British and Mughal architectural styles. It houses a museum with exhibits on India's colonial history, including paintings, manuscripts, and sculptures. The lush gardens surrounding the monument add to its charm.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item">
                <img src="/images/salar-jung-1920x1080.png">
                <div class="content">
                    <p>VISIT</p>
                    <h2>Salar Jung</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Salar Jung Museum in Hyderabad is one of India's largest museums, featuring an extensive collection of art, antiques, and artifacts from around the world. Highlights include Persian carpets, European sculptures, and intricate Indian carvings. The museum is famous for its diverse exhibits, showcasing the personal collection of Salar Jung III.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="item">
                <img src="/images/ins-1920x1080.jpg">
                <div class="content">
                    <p>VISIT</p>
                    <h2>INS Kursura</h2>
                    <p>
                        The INS Kursura Museum in Visakhapatnam is a unique submarine museum housed inside the decommissioned Indian Navy submarine, INS Kursura. Visitors can explore the inner workings of the submarine, learning about life aboard and the history of India's naval defense. It offers a rare glimpse into the technology and operations of submarines.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
